result.execSummary:
The defendant Brittany N Evans was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Statements made as to sentencing. 
Defendant ordered to serve 144 days in the House of Correction with credit of 144 days time served.  
Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges by 2.2.16 or, if not paid, a civil judgment is ordered.
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs by 2.2.16, or, if not paid, a civil judgment is ordered.

Defendant Brittany N Evans in court with attorney Gregory Roger Parr.  Defendant Brittany N Evans in custody.  Nathaniel E Adamson for Antonella Aleman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Amended information, filed, copy served on defendant. COUNT 1 is amended to OBSTRUCTING AN OFFICER, a CLASS A MISDEMEANOR, contrary to sec 946.61(1) 939.51(3)(a) Wis stats.  Defendant acknowledges receipt of amended information and waives formal reading.  Defendant changes plea to GUILTY as to amended charge. Defendant examined as to her plea, advised of her Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the amended information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.
